# Headless Dashboard Readiness

- In headless Playwright runs, use a fixed desktop viewport instead of relying on `viewport: null` so pages do not collapse into mobile/header variants.
- When a test validates desktop dashboard widgets like notification bell, search, user menu, or summary cards, prefer desktop-stable locators and avoid selectors that only work in responsive/mobile layouts.
- After navigating back to a dashboard page, wait for a stable dashboard-ready signal before asserting card values. Prefer visible summary-card headings or card values over immediate post-URL assertions.
- If a card label/value locator is flaky, anchor it to the card container around the heading rather than a brittle direct sibling path.

## Example Pattern

```typescript
const viewport = automationConfig.headless
  ? { width: 1440, height: 900 }
  : null;

await page.waitForURL(/\/rbox\/inventory\/dashboard/, { timeout: navigationTimeout });
await page.locator("xpath=//h6[normalize-space()='Sold Tickets Today']").first().waitFor({
  state: "visible",
  timeout: 60_000,
});
```
